# Comment Guidelines

Write self-documenting code. Avoid comments that add no value.

## Don't Write

```typescript
// ❌ Obvious - restates the code
i++; // increment i

// ❌ Explains "what" not "why"
const user = getUser(id); // get user by id

// ❌ Excessive
// This function calculates the sum
// It takes two numbers as parameters
// And returns their sum
function add(a, b) { return a + b; }
```

## Do Write

```typescript
// ✅ Explains non-obvious "why"
// Skip validation for admin users to allow bulk operations
if (user.isAdmin) return true;

// ✅ Documents complex business logic
// Price tiers: 0-100 units = base, 101-500 = 10% off, 500+ = 25% off

// ✅ Warns about gotchas
// IMPORTANT: Order matters - auth middleware must run before rate limiting
```

## Principles

- Code should be readable without comments
- Comment the "why", never the "what"
- If you need to explain what code does, refactor it instead
- Good names > explanatory comments
